{"award_age":46.0,"bio_image":"full\/272590ec79fa603f4f63d46b71044e9174ee6cc0.jpg","category":"Physics","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1933-05-03T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/9\/9f\/Steven_weinberg_2010.jpg\/220px-Steven_weinberg_2010.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Steven_Weinberg","mini_bio":"<p><b>Steven Weinberg<\/b> (born May 3, 1933) is an American <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Theoretical_physics\" title=\"Theoretical physics\">theoretical<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physicist\" title=\"Physicist\">physicist<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physics\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physics\">Nobel laureate in Physics<\/a> for his contributions with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Abdus_Salam\" title=\"Abdus Salam\">Abdus Salam<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sheldon_Lee_Glashow\" title=\"Sheldon Lee Glashow\">Sheldon Glashow<\/a> to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Electroweak_interaction\" title=\"Electroweak interaction\">unification<\/a> of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Weak_force\" title=\"Weak force\" class=\"mw-redirect\">weak force<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Electromagnetism\" title=\"Electromagnetism\">electromagnetic<\/a> interaction between elementary particles.<\/p><p>He holds the Josey Regental Chair in Science at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/University_of_Texas_at_Austin\" title=\"University of Texas at Austin\">University of Texas at Austin<\/a>, where he is a member of the Physics and Astronomy Departments. His research on elementary particles and cosmology has been honored with numerous prizes and awards, including in 1979 the Nobel Prize in Physics and in 1991 the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Medal_of_Science\" title=\"National Medal of Science\">National Medal of Science<\/a>. In 2004 he received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Benjamin_Franklin_Medal_(American_Philosophical_Society)\" title=\"Benjamin Franklin Medal (American Philosophical Society)\">Benjamin Franklin Medal<\/a> of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/American_Philosophical_Society\" title=\"American Philosophical Society\">American Philosophical Society<\/a>, with a citation that said he is \"considered by many to be the preeminent theoretical physicist alive in the world today.\" He has been elected to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/US_National_Academy_of_Sciences\" title=\"US National Academy of Sciences\" class=\"mw-redirect\">US National Academy of Sciences<\/a> and Britain's <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Royal_Society\" title=\"Royal Society\">Royal Society<\/a>, as well as to the American Philosophical Society and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/American_Academy_of_Arts_and_Sciences\" title=\"American Academy of Arts and Sciences\">American Academy of Arts and Sciences<\/a>.<\/p><p>Weinberg's articles on various subjects occasionally appear in <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_New_York_Review_of_Books\" title=\"The New York Review of Books\">The New York Review of Books<\/a><\/i> and other periodicals. He has served as consultant at the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/U._S._Arms_Control_and_Disarmament_Agency\" title=\"U. S. Arms Control and Disarmament Agency\" class=\"mw-redirect\">U. S. Arms Control and Disarmament Agency<\/a>, President of the Philosophical Society of Texas, and member of the Board of Editors of <i>Daedalus<\/i> magazine, the Council of Scholars of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Library_of_Congress\" title=\"Library of Congress\">Library of Congress<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/JASON_(advisory_group)\" title=\"JASON (advisory group)\">JASON<\/a> group of defense consultants, and many other boards and committees.<\/p>","name":"Steven Weinberg","place_of_birth":"New York, U.S.","place_of_death":null,"text":"Steven Weinberg , Physics, 1979","year":1979.0}